The latest Met department report indicates that the just ended rains were the highest in 70 years. The analysis shows weather stations received record rainfall, something that as a water deficit country we should be celebrating. But instead, the rains turned into a curse rather than a blessing. Deaths and destruction characterised the downpour and right now, the national and most county governments are grappling with the aftermath. Up to mid-May, 183 deaths had been recorded, 54 injured, 53,675 households affected with 225,360 people displaced, according to the National Disaster Operations Centre.    